# AKOS TechOps Discipline

Use this rule whenever authoring or reviewing artefacts that touch
**Vercel / Render / Supabase deploys**, **observability configuration**
(Sentry / Vercel Analytics / Render service status / external uptime
monitors), **security posture** (RLS / secret rotation / dependency
audit), **incident-response runbooks**, or **Core Web Vitals
measurement**. Codifies the mechanical layer of
[`TECHOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Tech/System Owner/canonicals/TECHOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
(Wave M P5 mint per D-IH-86-BX).

## When this rule applies

- Deploy to Vercel / Render / Supabase (any environment tier).
- Modify observability configuration (Sentry DSN, alert rules,
  trace sampling, log aggregation endpoints).
- Touch security posture (RLS policies, secret rotation runbooks,
  dependency upgrade PRs).
- Author or modify an incident-response runbook under
  `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Envoy Tech Lab/**/runbooks/`.
- Modify Core Web Vitals measurement infrastructure (Lighthouse CI
  config, Vercel Analytics config).

## RULE 1 — Production deploys must satisfy the 7 TechOps dimensions (binding)

Every production deploy (Vercel / Render / Supabase) must pass the
7 TechOps dimensions defined in
[`TECHOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Tech/System Owner/canonicals/TECHOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
§2 either pre-deploy or as part of the post-deploy verification:

- **TECH-01** Uptime SLO → external monitor reports last-30d ≥ 99.9%
- **TECH-02** Core Web Vitals → mobile P75 LCP < 2.5s, INP < 200ms,
  CLS < 0.1 on every public route
- **TECH-03** Error budget tracking → Sentry error rate within
  budget for the rolling 24h window
- **TECH-04** Deploy posture → previous deploy success + rollback
  target retained
- **TECH-05** Security posture → Supabase `get_advisors security`
  clean for any new schema; `npm audit` / `pip-audit` clean for
  dependency updates
- **TECH-06** Observability evidence → critical path has Sentry
  trace coverage + log emission
- **TECH-07** Incident management → runbook exists for the service;
  on-call rotation populated

Preview / staging tiers carry lighter thresholds per the canonical's
§3 tier modifier.

## RULE 2 — Hotfix workflow inherits the deploy-health contract (binding)

Hotfix deploys follow the validate-deploy contract from
`akos-deploy-health.mdc`: validate locally → deploy to preview →
smoke-test preview → promote to production → verify production
post-deploy. Each step has explicit operator-gate or automated-gate
classification per `akos-deploy-health.mdc`.

TechOps adds: every hotfix produces a Sev-2 (or higher) post-mortem
within 7 days per TECH-07, regardless of resolution speed. This is
the institutional learning surface that prevents repeat incidents.

## RULE 3 — Observability gaps must be tracked, not silently absorbed (binding)

When a critical path lacks Sentry trace coverage or log emission
(TECH-06), the gap must surface via:

- A row in `docs/wip/planning/_trackers/observability-coverage-tracker.md`
  (mint if not yet existing) with surface path + criticality + remediation
  owner + ETA.
- An OPS_REGISTER row tagged with appropriate area + persona pickup
  if the gap is meaningful enough to schedule.

Silent gaps are an anti-pattern; the discipline's purpose is to make
them legible so operator can disposition.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Internal dev / local-only environments (no production audience).
- Test fixtures or ephemeral artifacts.
- Documentation-only changes that do not affect runtime behaviour.

